<p>Whereas Japan has a plethora of vivid cultural traditions that are still kicking (some barely), what can you point to that the British have, aside from a couple of sports?</p>
<p>The Brits are probably called &#8220;poms&#8221; because of the decorations associated with their &#8220;pomp and ceremony&#8221;, which would appear to derive from a vacuous self-congratulatory celebration of their subjecting other peoples during the British Empire.</p>
<p>Kimono are only exotic to those not familiar with Japanese culture. Once you start studying the culture, the motifs start to make sense in a register beyond the merely impressionistic.</p>
