were made of denim woven at the Amoskeag Manufacturing Company in Manchester, New Hampshire. The cuff was functional in another way, too. Cowboys who spent hours and hours in the saddle found the cuffs handy as storage spaces: they could hold a tobacco pouch or pack of cigarettes, for example. It was a lot easier to reach into your cuff than your saddle bag, and you didn’t have to get off the horse to do it.<br />
The iconic Blue jeans have a history from 1873 with AMERICAN Cowboys and therefore an American historical item.<br />
If people have a problem with &#8220;culturally appropriating&#8221; the Kimono<br />
by having foreigners wear it then maybe they shouldn&#8217;t wear blue jeans<br />
which would be &#8220;culturally appropriating&#8221; something from my culture.<br />
